## Counter Cache

Optimize counting associated records.

```ruby
# app/models/article.rb
class Article < ApplicationRecord
  belongs_to :user, counter_cache: true
  # Updates user.articles_count automatically
end

# app/models/user.rb
class User < ApplicationRecord
  has_many :articles
  # Has articles_count column
end
```

**Migration:**
```ruby
class AddArticlesCountToUsers < ActiveRecord::Migration[8.0]
  def change
    add_column :users, :articles_count, :integer, default: 0, null: false
    
    # Reset existing counts
    User.find_each do |user|
      User.reset_counters(user.id, :articles)
    end
  end
end
```

**Custom counter cache:**
```ruby
class Article < ApplicationRecord
  belongs_to :user, counter_cache: :published_articles_count
end

# Requires published_articles_count column on users table
```

